theorem P3_iff_interiorClosure_mem_nhds {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 A ‚Üî ‚àÄ x ‚àà A, interior (closure A) ‚àà ùìù x := by
  classical
  constructor
  ¬∑ intro hP3 x hx
    have hx_int : x ‚àà interior (closure A) := hP3 hx
    exact (isOpen_interior.mem_nhds hx_int)
  ¬∑ intro h
    dsimp [Topology.P3]
    intro x hx
    have h_nhds : interior (closure A) ‚àà ùìù x := h x hx
    exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).2 h_nhds

theorem dense_implies_P3_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A ‚Üí Topology.P3 (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro hDense
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x _hx
  -- Since `A` is dense, its closure is the whole space.
  have h_closure : (closure A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa using hDense.closure_eq
  -- Consequently, the interior of this closure is also the whole space.
  have h_int : interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_closure, interior_univ]
  -- The goal follows immediately.
  simpa [h_int] using (Set.mem_univ x)

theorem P2_iff_interiorClosureInterior_mem_nhds

    Topology.P2 A ‚Üî ‚àÄ x ‚àà A, interior (closure (interior A)) ‚àà ùìù x := by
  classical
  constructor
  ¬∑ intro hP2 x hx
    have hxInt : x ‚àà interior (closure (interior A)) := hP2 hx
    exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).1 hxInt
  ¬∑ intro h
    dsimp [Topology.P2]
    intro x hx
    have hNhds : interior (closure (interior A)) ‚àà ùìù x := h x hx
    exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).2 hNhds
